
# 2026-03-16 12:39:31.702017
+Enhance the CRM dashboard with follow-up management.
+
+CHANGES NEEDED:
+
+1. Add fields to Contact interface (both files):
+   - followUpDate: string | null  (ISO date string)
+   - linkedInUrl: string | null
+   - programInterest: string | null  (e.g. 'transformation-program', 'bcba-exam-prep', etc.)
+
+2. API (route.ts): handle the new fields in POST and PATCH (include in newContact creation and merge).
+
+3. page.tsx — Follow-up Queue section (add ABOVE the contact grid):
+   - Show contacts where followUpDate is set
+   - Split into two groups: OVERDUE (date < today, red border) and UPCOMING THIS WEEK (date within 7 days, amber border)
+   - Each card: name, email, company/role, follow-up date, programInterest badge, quick action buttons (Email, LinkedIn if url set)
+   - If no follow-ups: show empty state 'No follow-ups scheduled'
+   - Collapsible section header showing count
+
+4. page.tsx — Add sort option: 'followUpDate-asc' = 'Most Urgent Follow-ups'
+
+5. page.tsx — Contact cards: show followUpDate if set with a Calendar icon + colored badge (red=overdue, amber=this week, green=later)
+
+6. page.tsx — Fix 'Edit Contact' button (currently just alerts). Replace the alert with a real edit modal that pre-fills all fields including the new ones. Add followUpDate datepicker and linkedInUrl text input to both add and edit modals.
+
+7. page.tsx — Add 'followUpDate' filter: 'Needs Follow-up Today', 'Overdue', 'This Week'
+
+IMPORTANT RULES:
+- No purple/violet/indigo colors anywhere - use emerald/amber/slate only
+- No sticky/fixed nav
+- No bold text in body paragraphs
+- No emojis in UI (use Lucide icons instead)
+- Keep all existing functionality intact

