# 2026-03-16 12:40:20.285984
+Enhance the CRM with follow-up management.
+
+CHANGES:
+
+1. Add to Contact interface (BOTH files): followUpDate: string | null, linkedInUrl: string | null, programInterest: string | null
+
+2. route.ts: include new fields in POST newContact and PATCH merge. Add followUpDate filter in GET: if filter param 'followUp=overdue', return contacts where followUpDate < today; if 'followUp=this-week', return within 7 days.
+
+3. page.tsx — Follow-up Queue: Add a collapsible section ABOVE the contact grid. Show contacts with followUpDate set, split into OVERDUE (red border, date past) and THIS WEEK (amber border, within 7 days). Each item shows: name, role/company, follow-up date, programInterest badge, mailto link, linkedInUrl link if set. Header shows counts. Empty state: 'No follow-ups scheduled'.
+
+4. page.tsx — Contact cards: add Calendar icon + followUpDate badge (red=overdue, amber=this week, slate=future) when followUpDate is set.
+
+5. page.tsx — Fix Edit button (currently alerts). Replace with real edit modal pre-filling all fields. Add followUpDate (input type=date) and linkedInUrl (text input) and programInterest (text input) to both Add and Edit modals.
+
+6. page.tsx — Add sort option 'followUpDate-asc' labeled 'Upcoming Follow-ups'.
+
+RULES: no purple/violet/indigo. Use emerald/amber/slate/red only. No emojis in UI. No sticky nav. No bold in body text. Keep all existing functionality.

